1. void *realloc (void *ptr, size_t size)
   1) NULL is returned,
      a) if the size is zero and the buffer argument is not NULL
      -- free the previous memory
      b) if there is not enough available memory to expand the block to the given size. 
      -- keep the previous memory
   2) new addr is returned
      -- free the previous memory
   3) addr unchanged

2. other memory functions
   1) void *malloc(size_t size)
   2) void *calloc(size_t nmemb, size_t size)
   3) void free(void *ptr)

3. memory management checker
   1) MEMWATCH
   2) YAMD
   3) Electric Fence
   4) Valgrind

4. MEMWATCH -- Please see the ToolKit demonstration

5. YAMD / Electric Fence (skipped)

6. Valgrind
